    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i just got a prescription for clarithromycin for my sinuses but i already take simvastatin for my cholesterol every night. is it okay to take them both or do i need to wait a few hours between doses?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Clarithromycin is a known inhibitor of CYP3A4, the enzyme responsible for metabolizing simvastatin, which can lead to dangerously high levels of simvastatin in your blood and increase your risk of severe muscle damage. You should not take these two medications together without first consulting your doctor or pharmacist, as they may need to adjust your simvastatin dose or switch to a different statin. Please call your healthcare provider immediately to discuss this interaction before taking your next dose.",
